- 'Specific data center' refers to the data center with the ID of 1; 
- 'Latest memory metrics' implies the most recent memory usage data available for each server;
- 'Active alerts' are those with an alert status of 'active'.

Threshold values are predefined limits for memory metrics; 
Metric types (e.g., VSDCMIN, VSDCMAX) refer to different aspects of memory metrics; 
Servers are identified by server names and have IP addresses; 
Servers are located in data centers; 
Alert messages are triggered when threshold values are exceeded.

sql:
SELECT MIN(value) AS min_value
FROM memory_metrics
WHERE metric_type = 'VSDCMIN';
